One Fidelity Security official was injured on Tuesday afternoon after an attack on his cash-in-transit van, Lowvelder reported. Allegations are that about 10 suspects who were driving in four vehicles, a black Mercedes, two BMWs, one grey and one black, as well as a white bakkie, opened fire at the Fidelity Security armoured bakkie, which was coming from Malalane side and heading towards Mbombela until it came to halt. A witness managed to capture the moment the robbers blew the cash-in-transit van. The suspects escaped with an undisclosed amount of cash.Watch video below: